5/3/2022, updated on 27/11/2024: Election Commission of Malaysia (SPR), Tindak Malaysia (2024), Attorney General Chambers, Utusan Borneo (https://www.utusanborneo.com.my/2020/01/19/ph-ambil-iktibar-keputusan-prk-kimanis)

This is the official result of the non-gazetted SPR. The original Election Results PDF hosted on EC's website has been removed. While Sabah's new Redelineated boundaries were approved in the Dewan Rakyat on 17th July 2019, the 13th Schedule of the Malaysian Constitution states that new redelineated boundaries come into effect upon the dissolution of Dewan Rakyat or DUN (where 2018 Sabah DUN was dissolved with a gazette on 30th July 2020). Results match with Government Gazette P.U. (B) 44/2020. TindakMalaysia Network Services PLT is not responsible for any errors or omissions arising from the original data or its derivatives
